Before I start in though, I'd like say that The Grey was most likly nerfed becuase of druid and necro epics making encounters so trivial, there was very little mana spent, and very little risk.<br>
<br>
....In any case, I do see the problems associated with how they went about fixing this issue.  One of my biggest gripes about these things is not so much that they nerfed the zone....it's more along the lines of what you said, it's a signal they are sending us.  That signal being that Verant wants wizards to group.  The only problem with that, is that we are strictly damage machines, there's nothing to offset us when it comes to group utility spells.  <br>
<br>
My opinion is that quad kiting is bug in EQ, it's just something that Verant choose not to fix.  Now that they are trying to get rid of quad kiting, they should offset that by adding some group friendly utility spells.<br>
